    {
      "id": "14",
      "type": "voice_bot",
      "name": "qualification_brain",
      "triggeredBy": [
        "unreadMessage.fromAll"
      ],
      "responseType": "json",
      "staticId": 14,
      "position": {
        "x": 1693,
        "y": 582
      },
      "isGoal": false,
      "goalName": null,
      "nodeConfig": {
        "actionType": "prompt",
        "prompt": "# TASK: Extract Qualification Data\n\nYou are working for Apex Motors, a luxury automotive dealership. Your job is to read the ENTIRE conversation history and extract all available data points.\n\nExtract ALL of the following variables from the conversation. ONLY extract if the customer EXPLICITLY states the information. If a data point hasn't been mentioned yet, set the value to \"UNSPECIFIED\". DO NOT infer, assume, or guess values based on context.\n\n---\n\n## CUSTOMER INTENT\n\n**stock_preference:**\n- \"NEW\" if customer says: \"new\", \"new car\", \"new vehicle\", \"brand new\", \"new model\"\n- \"PRE-OWNED\" if customer says: \"used\", \"pre-owned\", \"certified pre-owned\", \"second-hand\"\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if they only said \"car\" or \"vehicle\" without the word \"new\" or \"used\"\n\nCRITICAL: Search the ENTIRE conversation history. If the customer said \"new\" ANYWHERE in the conversation, extract stock_preference=\"NEW\".\n\nExamples:\n- \"I want to buy a car\" (first message) → \"UNSPECIFIED\"\n- \"I'd like to buy a new car\" (second message) → \"NEW\" (they said \"new\"!)\n- \"A new one\" → \"NEW\"\n\n---\n\n## CUSTOMER INFORMATION\n\n**customer_name:**\n- Full name if they introduced themselves (\"Hi, I'm John Smith\")\n- First name if only first name given\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n\n**customer_email:**\n- Email address if they provide it during conversation\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n- Note: Unlikely in voice calls, but capture if mentioned\n\n---\n\n## IF CUSTOMER_INTENT IS \"SALES\":\n\n**stock_preference:**\n- \"NEW\" for new vehicles (only if explicitly mentioned: \"new car\", \"new vehicle\", \"brand new\")\n- \"PRE-OWNED\" for used or certified pre-owned vehicles (only if explicitly mentioned: \"used\", \"pre-owned\", \"certified pre-owned\")\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned or just said \"car\" or \"vehicle\" without specifying\n- Example: \"I want to buy a car\" → stock_preference = \"UNSPECIFIED\" (not specified)\n- Example: \"I want a new car\" → stock_preference = \"NEW\"\n\n**budget_range:**\n- Their stated budget as a string (e.g., \"$60,000\", \"$50K-70K\", \"under $100,000\")\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n- CRITICAL: Extract the value if the customer states a numeric value, spelled-out number, or formatted price for their budget.\n- DO NOT infer budget from vehicle type (luxury, economy, new, used)\n- Examples that DO NOT contain budget: \"I want to buy a car\", \"I need a new vehicle\", \"Looking for something nice\"\n\n**has_trade_in:**\n- \"YES\" if they have a vehicle to trade in\n- \"NO\" if they explicitly say no trade-in or paying cash with no trade\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n\n**timeline:**\n- \"THIS_WEEK\" if buying within the next 7 days\n- \"THIS_MONTH\" if buying within 1-4 weeks\n- \"NEXT_MONTH_OR_TWO\" if buying within 2-3 months\n- \"RESEARCHING\" if no specific timeline or 4+ months out\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n\n---\n\n## IF CUSTOMER_INTENT IS \"SERVICE\":\n\n**job_type:**\n- \"MAINTENANCE\" for routine service (oil change, tire rotation, inspection)\n- \"REPAIR\" for fixing problems (check engine light, brakes, unusual noises)\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n\n**service_lane:**\n- \"EXPRESS\" if job_type is \"MAINTENANCE\"\n- \"DIAGNOSTIC\" if job_type is \"REPAIR\"\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if job_type is \"UNSPECIFIED\"\n\n**logistics:**\n- \"WAIT\" if customer wants to wait at dealership\n- \"DROP_OFF\" if customer wants to drop off vehicle\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if not mentioned\n\n**loaner_eligible:**\n- \"YES\" if job_type is \"REPAIR\" AND logistics is \"DROP_OFF\"\n- \"NO\" otherwise\n- \"UNSPECIFIED\" if we don't know yet\n\n---\n\n## IMPORTANT RULES:\n\n1. **Extract ALL variables on every message** - Even if most are \"UNSPECIFIED\"\n\n2. **Read the ENTIRE conversation history** - Customer may have given multiple answers\n\n3. **Handle out-of-order answers** - If they say \"I want a new car with a trade-in for $50K this week\", extract all four: stock_preference=\"NEW\", has_trade_in=\"YES\", budget_range=\"$50,000\", timeline=\"THIS_WEEK\"\n\n4. **Intent Switching**: If the customer explicitly changes their goal (e.g., \"Forget the car, I need an oil change\"), update customer_intent immediately. Retain all previously extracted variables from the former intent. The active path is determined solely by the current customer_intent.\n\n5. **CRITICAL - State Persistence**: This is THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE. Once a variable has a value other than \"UNSPECIFIED\", you MUST keep that value in ALL future extractions unless the customer explicitly contradicts it.\n\nExamples of what KEEPS the value:\n- stock_preference = \"NEW\", user says \"Yes\" → KEEP stock_preference = \"NEW\"\n- stock_preference = \"PRE-OWNED\", user says \"Sounds good\" → KEEP stock_preference = \"PRE-OWNED\"  \n- budget_range = \"$50,000\", user says \"Okay\" → KEEP budget_range = \"$50,000\"\n\nExamples of what CHANGES the value (explicit contradiction):\n- stock_preference = \"NEW\", user says \"Actually, I want used\" → CHANGE to stock_preference = \"PRE-OWNED\"\n- budget_range = \"$50K\", user says \"No, $70K\" → CHANGE to budget_range = \"$70,000\"\n\nIf the current message doesn't mention a variable, but you extracted it in a previous message, YOU MUST COPY THE PREVIOUS VALUE. Do NOT reset to \"UNSPECIFIED\".\n\n6. **\"UNSPECIFIED\" means \"not mentioned yet\"** - Not \"unknown\" or \"not applicable\"\n\n7. **Service_lane is auto-calculated** - Don't ask about it, just derive from job_type\n\n8. **Loaner_eligible is auto-calculated** - Don't ask about it, just derive from job_type + logistics\n\n9. **Passive extraction only for name and email** - Extract if mentioned naturally, don't force it.\n\n---\n\nDo NOT engage in conversation. Do NOT ask questions. Just extract data and return the JSON.",
        "responseSchema": {
          "type": "object",
          "required": [
            "job_type",
            "timeline",
            "logistics",
            "budget_range",
            "has_trade_in",
            "service_lane",
            "customer_name",
            "customer_email",
            "customer_intent",
            "loaner_eligible",
            "stock_preference"
          ],
          "properties": {
            "job_type": {
              "enum": [
                "MAINTENANCE",
                "REPAIR",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Type of service needed (SERVICE path only)"
            },
            "timeline": {
              "enum": [
                "THIS_WEEK",
                "THIS_MONTH",
                "NEXT_MONTH_OR_TWO",
                "RESEARCHING",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "When customer wants to purchase (SALES path)"
            },
            "logistics": {
              "enum": [
                "WAIT",
                "DROP_OFF",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Whether customer waits or drops off vehicle (SERVICE path)"
            },
            "budget_range": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Customer's stated budget (e.g., \"$60,000\")"
            },
            "has_trade_in": {
              "enum": [
                "YES",
                "NO",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Whether customer has a vehicle to trade in (SALES path)"
            },
            "service_lane": {
              "enum": [
                "EXPRESS",
                "DIAGNOSTIC",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Auto-calculated from job_type"
            },
            "customer_name": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Customer's full name if mentioned"
            },
            "customer_email": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Customer's email if mentioned"
            },
            "customer_intent": {
              "enum": [
                "SALES",
                "SERVICE",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Customer's intent - SALES for buying, SERVICE for maintenance/repair"
            },
            "loaner_eligible": {
              "enum": [
                "YES",
                "NO",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Auto-calculated: YES if REPAIR + DROP_OFF"
            },
            "stock_preference": {
              "enum": [
                "NEW",
                "PRE-OWNED",
                "UNSPECIFIED"
              ],
              "type": "string",
              "description": "New vehicle or pre-owned (SALES path only)"
            }
          }
        },
        "responseToolName": "extraction_complete",
        "responseToolDescription": "Call this function immediately after extracting all variables. This function should be called on EVERY user message to update the extraction state.",
        "allowInterruptions": true,
        "disableRepeatOnSilence": false,
        "shouldLoop": true,
        "waitForSpeech": false,
        "inactivity": {},
        "ivr": {
          "name": null,
          "description": null,
          "canNavigateToNode": false,
          "canNavigateFromNode": false
        }
      }
    },
